From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] avfilter: add vmaf_pre filter (learned pre-processing)

New video filter `vmaf_pre` that runs a tiny residual CNN (C3 in Lusoris
libvmaf's tiny-AI matrix) to pre-process frames before encoding. The
filter loads an ONNX model via libvmaf's shared DNN runtime (ONNX
Runtime) and applies an identity-plus-residual transform that clamps to
[0,1] in normalized space. Intended for denoise / deblock / perceptual-
sharpener learned filters shipped under model/tiny/filter_*.onnx.

Options:
  model   - path to .onnx learned-filter model (required)
  device  - auto | cpu | cuda | openvino | rocm (default: auto)
  threads - CPU EP intra-op threads (default: 0)

Links against libvmaf for the inference primitives only — no scoring
path is exercised. Requires libvmaf built with --enable_dnn.

Status: DRAFT. Needs rebase against upstream master before submission.

Signed-off-by: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
